1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:08,849
A retired owner-manager of a medium-sized printing company, sixty employees, explained to me how his successor was picked.

2
00:00:09,440 --> 00:00:16,849
Five years ago, my friend began, I needed an accountant to head up our accounting and office routine.

3
00:00:17,040 --> 00:00:21,250
The fellow I hired was named Harry and was only twenty-six.

4
00:00:21,359 --> 00:00:26,369
He knew nothing about the printing business, but his record showed he was a good accountant.

5
00:00:26,480 --> 00:00:33,010
Yet, a year and a half ago, when I retired, we made him president and general manager of the company.

6
00:00:33,440 --> 00:00:38,450
Looking back on it, Harry had one trait that put him out in front of everyone else.

7
00:00:38,720 --> 00:00:46,129
Harry was sincerely and actively interested in the whole company, not just writing checks and keeping records.

8
00:00:46,320 --> 00:00:51,090
Whenever he saw how he could help other employees, he jumped right in.

9
00:00:51,599 --> 00:00:55,169
The first year Harry was with me, we lost a few men.

10
00:00:55,440 --> 00:01:02,050
Harry came to me with a fringe benefit program which he promised would cut down turnover at low cost.

11
00:01:02,160 --> 00:01:03,330
And it worked.

12
00:01:04,000 --> 00:01:09,490
Harry did many other things, too, which helped the whole company, not just this department.

13
00:01:09,680 --> 00:01:18,609
He made a detailed cost study of our production department and showed me how a $30,000 investment in new machinery would pay off.

14
00:01:19,040 --> 00:01:22,210
Once, we experienced a pretty bad sales slump.

15
00:01:22,320 --> 00:01:28,530
Harry went to our sales manager and said, in effect, I don't know much about the sales end of the business,

16
00:01:28,560 --> 00:01:30,050
but let me try to help.

17
00:01:30,240 --> 00:01:31,250
And he did.

18
00:01:31,440 --> 00:01:36,210
Harry came up with several good ideas, which helped us sell more jobs.

19
00:01:36,480 --> 00:01:41,889
When a new employee joined us, Harry was right there to help the fellow get comfortable.

20
00:01:42,160 --> 00:01:45,649
Harry took a real interest in the entire operation.

21
00:01:45,920 --> 00:01:50,930
When I retired, Harry was the only logical person to take over.

22
00:01:51,359 --> 00:01:54,369
But don't misunderstand, my friend continued.

23
00:01:54,640 --> 00:01:57,649
Harry didn't try to put himself over on me.

24
00:01:57,760 --> 00:01:59,490
He wasn't a mere meddler.

25
00:01:59,520 --> 00:02:02,050
He wasn't aggressive in a negative way.

26
00:02:02,160 --> 00:02:06,530
He didn't stab people in the back, and he didn't go around giving orders.

27
00:02:06,720 --> 00:02:08,770
He just went around helping.

28
00:02:09,040 --> 00:02:13,169
Harry simply acted as if everything in the company affected him.

29
00:02:13,440 --> 00:02:16,369
He made company business his business.

30
00:02:17,520 --> 00:02:20,290
We can all learn a lesson from Harry.

31
00:02:20,480 --> 00:02:26,129
The I'm-doing-my-job-and-that's-enough attitude is small, negative thinking.

32
00:02:26,480 --> 00:02:33,970
Big thinkers see themselves as members of a team effort, as winning or losing with the team, not by themselves.

33
00:02:34,240 --> 00:02:41,169
They help in every way they can, even when there is no direct and immediate compensation or other reward.

34
00:02:41,599 --> 00:02:46,290
The fellow who shrugs off a problem outside his own department with the comment,

35
00:02:46,480 --> 00:02:53,730
well, that's no concern of mine, let them worry about it, hasn't got the attitude it takes for top leadership.

36
00:02:54,320 --> 00:02:55,570
Practice this.

37
00:02:55,760 --> 00:02:58,050
Practice being a big thinker.

38
00:02:58,320 --> 00:03:02,050
See the company's interest as identical with your own.

39
00:03:02,320 --> 00:03:09,970
Probably only a very few persons working in large companies have a sincere, unselfish interest in their company.

40
00:03:10,160 --> 00:03:19,970
But after all, only a relatively few persons qualify as big thinkers, and these few are the ones eventually rewarded with the most responsible,

41
00:03:20,080 --> 00:03:21,730
best-paying jobs.

